New rap phenomenon Sho Madjozi and Inxeba (The Wound) actor Nakhane Touré will perform at the New York edition of the popular Afropunk festival in August 2018. Afropunk announced on Wednesday that the artists will be performing at the event. Nakhane and Sho Madjozi aren’t the only South African acts that will be performing at international festivals this year, Goldfish and Black Coffee will be playing at Coachella 2018. Different artists that will be performing at the event took to social media to express their delight. AFROPUNK BROOKLYN.  pic.twitter.com/WI1jLSIIST — Smi (@smino) March 27, 2018 -TNA Reporter